Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Quarter @lemon{1}. Halve @tomato{1} and slice into half-moons; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} to a hot large pan. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, ~{2%minutes}.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Add to pan with onion; season with @shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

While chicken cooks, in a large #bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of lemon. (Save the rest for another use.)

Add @spinach{2.5%ounce} and toss; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

Place dressed spinach in a line on the bottom half of each tortilla. Top with tomato, chicken, and @feta cheese{1/2%cup} (you may have some filling left over––save and serve on the side).

Fold and roll up tortillas to form wraps. Halve on a diagonal. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{3%ounce} and @hummus{1/2%cup} for dipping on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

> This fabulously fast and flavorful wrap is packed with juicy shawarma-seasoned sautéed chicken, salty-savory feta cheese, juicy tomato slices, and wholesome fresh spinach tossed in a garlicky dressing along with a bright squeeze of fresh lemon juice. It's served with a side of crunchy blue corn tortilla chips and creamy hummus for dipping. You feta believe it—this quick and filling meal will be on your table in just 15 minutes!